I've been seeing dermatologists all around town for the past 15 years for a variety of skin problems that have been very frustrating and challenging.
Dr. Schreiber has been my current provider for the past 2-3 years.
His office is certainly on the older side, but clean (which is a MUST for a doctor's office).
Couple TV's in the waiting area and plenty of literature in the exam rooms.
I've met most of the staff at one point or another and they have all been friendly and helpful.
I have noticed a high turnover rate during the past couple years, but as long as it doesn't affect patient care, it's no big deal to me.
He does have interns from Touro University do rotations at his practice that see patients (before he does) and help with procedures, you can refuse their involvement in your care at any time.
He has the shortest wait times I've ever experienced in any doctor's office.
And the rare times I do wait a bit longer, he apologizes with sincerity.
I can tell he is kind of an efficiency master.
Some people can perceive this as being rushed, so I can see why those couple negative reviews are there.
Because of that, he is not for everybody, but for most of us he is a great and brilliant doctor.
So just always know your history and be clear about what you're coming in for, basically "straight to the point" sort of deal.
Another one of my favorite things about him is his sense of humor, it takes a lot to make me laugh, and he does it almost every time I come in!
Definitely makes my skin problems a bit easier to deal with.
He is definitely a character, but I think most geniuses are.
I like characters, and he certainly knows what he's doing so I'll continue to see him as long as he keeps my problems in control.
It's very hard to find a doctor that is that skilled, cares about his/her patients, and is sympathetic to their situations.
It's usually just one or none of those things.

I have been a patient of Dr. Schreiber since moving here to Las Vegas 4 yrs ago.
He is a bit quirky and his office is a little old, but the man is very good.
He moves at a very quick pace which sometimes bothers some of his patients.
I was so lucky to find him.
He discovered a pre-cancerous patch of skin on the back of my arm that i did not even know was there.
